  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali148-kilavi">itu "veḷippaṭai tāṉē kaṟpiṉo ṭoppiṉu ñāṅkark kiḷanta mūṉṟu poruḷāka varaiyātu pirital kiḻavōṟ killai" eṉpataṉāṉ aracaṉ maṇkōṭaṟku ēvutaliṉ vāḷāṇetirum piriviṉkaṭ ṭalaivaṉ varaiviṭai vaittu vēntaṟkuṟṟuḻip pirintuḻi avaḷ varutta mikuti kaṇṭār kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali148">
              <l>tolliyaṉ ñālattut toḻilāṟṟi ñāyiṟu</l>
              <l>vallavaṉ kūṟiya viṉaitalai vaittāṉpōṟ</l>
              <l>kallaṭaipu katirūṉṟik kaṇpayaṅ keṭappeyara</l>
              <l>vallatu keṭuppava ṉaruḷkoṇṭa mukampōla</l>
              <l>mallaṉīrt tiraiyūrpu māliruṇ maticīppa</l>
              <l>villava roḻukkampō liruṅkaḻi malarkūmpac</l>
              <l>cellumeṉ ṉuyirppuṟat tiṟuttanta maruṇmālai;</l>
              <l rend="space">mālainī,</l>
              <l>iṉpūṟṟārk kiṟaicciyā yiyaivatō ceytāyma</l>
              <l>ṉaṉpūṟṟā raḻanītta vallaluṭ kalaṅkiya</l>
              <l>tuṉpuṟṟārt tuyarceyta ṟakkatō niṉakku;</l>
              <l rend="space">mālainī,</l>
              <l>kalantavar kāmattaik kaṉaṟṟalō ceytāyma</l>
              <l>ṉalaṅkoṇṭu nalkātār naṉinītta pulampiṉka</l>
              <l>ṇalantavark kaṇaṅkāta ṟakkatō niṉakku;</l>
              <l rend="space">mālainī,</l>
              <l>eṅkēḷvaṟ ṟarutalun tarukallāy tuṇaiyallai</l>
              <l>pirintavarkku nōyākip puṇarntavarkkup puṇaiyākit</l>
              <l>tiruntāta ceyiṉallā lillaiyō niṉakku;</l>
              <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
              <l>āyiḻai maṭavara lavala makalap </l>
              <l>pāyiruṭ parappiṉaip pakalkaḷain tatupōlap</l>
              <l>pōyavar maṇvauvi vantaṉar</l>
              <l>cēyuṟai kātalar ceyviṉai muṭittē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
              <l>While the sun, having performed [its] task in the world of ancient nature,</l>
              <l>like an able man who has taken on the work he talked about,</l>
              <l>goes back, settling in the rocks [and] leaning on [its] rays so that the yield of the eye is lost,</l>
              <l>while like the gracious face of the one who destroys what is not(?)</l>
              <l>the moon sweeps away the dark darkness, mounting the waves of the rich water,</l>
              <l>while the blossoms close in the dark backwaters like according to the conduct of householders,</l>
              <l corresp="1-7">my life goes in obscure evening that camps outside.</l>
              <l>Evening,</l>
              <l>being something pleasurable to those who feel pleasure, did you really do something agreeable?</l>
              <l>Is it befitting for you to cause misery in those who feel distress,</l>
              <l corresp="8-11">whose minds are upset by unhappiness when those who feel love were left [them] so that they cry? </l>
              <l>Evening,</l>
              <l>did you really cause those who mingled to burn passion?</l>
              <l>Is it befitting to you to become a torment to those who suffer</l>
              <l corresp="12-15">in loneliness when much left by those who took [their] beauty [and] do not grant [their] presence?</l>
              <l>Evening, </l>
              <l>you who do not bring our kinsman are of no help.</l>
              <l>Being pain for those who are separated, being a prop for those united,</l>
              <l corresp="16-19">unless you do imperfect things(?), is it not for you?</l>
              <l corresp="20">That is to say,</l>
              <l>so that the affliction of the simple girl with choice bangles departed,</l>
              <l>going like the day removing the expanse of spreading darkness</l>
              <l>having snatched land he came [back],</l>
              <l corresp="21-24">the lover who had stayed at a distance, accomplishing the work to be done.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
